  "prompt": "How can you tell who has viewed Instagram videos?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you cannot see exactly who has viewed your videos. Here's what you can see:\n\n1. For Instagram Stories:\n- You can see the total number of views\n- You can see a list of people who have viewed the story\n- This list is available only while the story is still active\n\n2. For Instagram Reels and standard posts:\n- You can see the total number of views\n- You cannot see individual viewer names\n- Only the total view count is displayed\n\n3. For IGTV videos:\n- You can see the total number of views\n- No individual viewer information is available\n\nInstagram intentionally limits viewer details to protect user privacy, so there's no built-in way to see exactly who watched your specific video content.",
